This paper is primarily focused on software-defined networking (SDN) and network optimization, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). However, the paper also discusses the use of high-level abstractions and optimization techniques, which could potentially fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and programming languages (cs.PL).
